Here is the Julia code for cleaning up a column name:

```julia
function clean_column(col::String)
    # Lowercase the column name
    col = lowercase(col);

    # Replace spaces and hyphens with underscores
    col = replace(col, " " => "_");
    col = replace(col, "-" => "_");

    return col;
end
```
This function first converts the column name to lowercase using `lowercase()` function. Then it replaces any space or hyphen with an underscore using `replace()`. This is done twice in case there are multiple spaces or hyphens present in the string. The cleaned up column name is then returned from this function.

You can use this function as follows:
```julia
col = "My Column";
clean_column(col);
```
This will output `"my_column"`.
